<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4895364>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. The highly differentiated endophyte in Treubia pygmaea R.M.Schust.. A, B, D. Scanning electron micrographs. C, E, F. Transmission electron micrographs. A. Profile of thallus showing the intercellular fungal zone (ef) and the intracellular zone below it (if). B, C. Details of the intracellular fungus showing hyphal coils (h), fungal lumps (l) and a degenerating lump (dl). D, E. Intracellular fungus showing pseudoparenchymatous hyphae (arrowed). F. Fungal spores (s) with multilayered walls in the intercellular mucilage (*). Scale bars = (A) 200 µm; (B, D) 20 µm; (C, E, F) 5 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4895364/files/figure.png" .

